    <item>
      <title>Getting started</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/installation-upgrade/getting-started/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/installation-upgrade/getting-started/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Follow these steps to configure and run NGINX Agent and a mock interface (&amp;ldquo;control plane&amp;rdquo;) to which NGINX Agent will report.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;install-nginx&#34;&gt;Install NGINX  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#install-nginx&#34; title=&#34;Install NGINX&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Follow the steps in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.nginx.com/nginx/admin-guide/installing-nginx/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Installation&lt;/a&gt; section to download, install, and run NGINX.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;clone-the-nginx-agent-repository&#34;&gt;Clone the NGINX Agent Repository  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#clone-the-nginx-agent-repository&#34; title=&#34;Clone the NGINX Agent Repository&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Using your preferred method, clone the NGINX Agent repository into your development directory. See &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/creating-and-managing-repositories/cloning-a-repository&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Cloning a GitHub Repository&lt;/a&gt; for additional help.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Installation from GitHub release</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/installation-upgrade/installation-github/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/installation-upgrade/installation-github/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn how to install NGINX Agent from a GitHub Release.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;install-nginx&#34;&gt;Install NGINX  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#install-nginx&#34; title=&#34;Install NGINX&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;NGINX Agent interfaces directly with an NGINX server process installed on the same system. If you don&amp;rsquo;t have it already, follow these steps to install &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.nginx.com/resources/wiki/start/topics/tutorials/install/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;NGINX Open Source&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.nginx.com/nginx/admin-guide/installing-nginx/installing-nginx-plus/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;NGINX Plus&lt;/a&gt;. Once installed, ensure the NGINX instance is running.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;install-nginx-agent-from-package-files&#34;&gt;Install NGINX Agent from Package Files  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#install-nginx-agent-from-package-files&#34; title=&#34;Install NGINX Agent from Package Files&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;To install NGINX Agent on your system, go to &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/nginx/agent/releases&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;GitHub Releases&lt;/a&gt; and download the latest package supported by your OS distribution and CPU architecture.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Installation from NGINX repository</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/installation-upgrade/installation-oss/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/installation-upgrade/installation-oss/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn how to install NGINX Agent from the NGINX Open Source repository.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#prerequisites&#34; title=&#34;Prerequisites&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;NGINX installed. Once installed, ensure it is running. If you don&amp;rsquo;t have it installed already, follow these steps to install &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.nginx.com/nginx/admin-guide/installing-nginx/installing-nginx-open-source/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;NGINX&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/technical-specifications/#supported-distributions&#34;&gt;supported operating system and architecture&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;root&lt;/code&gt; privilege&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;configure-nginx-oss-repository-for-installing-nginx-agent&#34;&gt;Configure NGINX OSS Repository for installing NGINX Agent  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#configure-nginx-oss-repository-for-installing-nginx-agent&#34; title=&#34;Configure NGINX OSS Repository for installing NGINX Agent&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Before you install NGINX Agent for the first time on your system, you need to set up the &lt;code&gt;nginx-agent&lt;/code&gt; packages repository. Afterward, you can install and update NGINX Agent from the repository.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Installation from NGINX Plus repository</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/installation-upgrade/installation-plus/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/installation-upgrade/installation-plus/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn how to install NGINX Agent from NGINX Plus repository&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#prerequisites&#34; title=&#34;Prerequisites&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;An NGINX Plus subscription (purchased or trial)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;NGINX Plus installed. Once installed, ensure it is running. If you don&amp;rsquo;t have it installed already, follow these steps to install &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.nginx.com/nginx/admin-guide/installing-nginx/installing-nginx-plus/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;NGINX Plus&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/technical-specifications/#supported-distributions&#34;&gt;supported operating system and architecture&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;root&lt;/code&gt; privilege&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Your credentials to the MyF5 Customer Portal, provided by email from F5, Inc.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Your NGINX Plus certificate and public key (&lt;code&gt;nginx-repo.crt&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;nginx-repo.key&lt;/code&gt; files), provided by email from F5, Inc.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;configure-nginx-plus-repository-for-installing-nginx-agent&#34;&gt;Configure NGINX Plus Repository for installing NGINX Agent  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#configure-nginx-plus-repository-for-installing-nginx-agent&#34; title=&#34;Configure NGINX Plus Repository for installing NGINX Agent&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Before you install NGINX Agent for the first time on your system, you need to set up the &lt;code&gt;nginx-agent&lt;/code&gt; packages repository. Afterward, you can install and update NGINX Agent from the repository.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Run without root privileges</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/installation-upgrade/installation-unprivileged/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/installation-upgrade/installation-unprivileged/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;If the policies of your organization do not allow running processes as root, you can run NGINX Agent under a user without root privileges.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This also aligns with the principle of least privilege, which is a security concept that limits the access rights of users to the bare minimum permissions they need to perform their work.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;before-you-begin&#34;&gt;Before you begin  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#before-you-begin&#34; title=&#34;Before you begin&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Please note that &lt;strong&gt;root access is required to install NGINX Agent&lt;/strong&gt;. The agent can be run under a non-root user after the installation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
