      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-agent/installation-upgrade/upgrade/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Learn how to upgrade NGINX Agent.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;upgrade-nginx-agent-from-version-v2310-or-greater&#34;&gt;Upgrade NGINX Agent from version v2.31.0 or greater  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#upgrade-nginx-agent-from-version-v2310-or-greater&#34; title=&#34;Upgrade NGINX Agent from version v2.31.0 or greater&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt; Starting from version v2.31.0, NGINX Agent will automatically restart itself during an upgrade.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;To upgrade NGINX Agent, follow these steps:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Open an SSH connection to the server where you’ve installed NGINX Agent and log in.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Make a backup copy of the following locations to ensure that you can successfully recover if the upgrade has issues:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
